{"id":"compose-user-profile","domain":"social","difficulty":"hard","pass":true,"score":1,"reasoning":"All 5 MSS fields match exactly","expected":{"contentType":"social-identity","structure":"wall","mechanics":["follow"],"boundary":"ask","scale":3},"actual":"```json\n{\"contentType\":\"social-identity\",\"structure\":\"wall\",\"mechanics\":[\"follow\"],\"boundary\":\"ask\",\"scale\":3}\n```\n\n**Reasoning:**\n\n- **contentType: `social-identity`** — Prevents auto-grouping with the `social` feed. Profiles are owned by individuals and shouldn't be manipulated alongside feed content. The hyphenated variant signals different interaction semantics.\n- **structure: `wall`** — Combines static profile info (bio, avatar) with a chronological activity stream. This is the defining pattern for `wall`: user profile + owned activity.\n- **mechanics: `[\"follow\"]`** — Only following activates on profiles. Likes, shares, and posts live on the feed itself, not here.\n- **boundary: `ask`** — Inherits from parent feed context. Profile data (identity, activity) requires user consent before sharing to connected modules.\n- **scale: 3** — A block composing multiple S2 groups (bio object, avatar object, activity stream). It's an interactive unit with emergent dynamics (following triggers subscription), but not a complete module by itself (S5).","durationMs":5109}
{"id":"compose-tools-dashboard","domain":"tools","difficulty":"hard","pass":false,"score":0.8,"reasoning":"4/5 fields correct. Mismatches: structure (expected: \"collection\", got: \"pool\")","expected":{"contentType":"tools","structure":"collection","mechanics":["filter"],"boundary":"none","scale":3},"actual":"```json\n{\"contentType\":\"tools\",\"structure\":\"pool\",\"mechanics\":[\"filter\"],\"boundary\":\"none\",\"scale\":3}\n```\n\n**Reasoning:**\n- **contentType: \"tools\"** — All three S2 modules are `tools`, so the dashboard inherits their grouping\n- **structure: \"pool\"** — A hierarchical grouping of the three tool modules (garden planner, seed inventory, calendar) under one dashboard\n- **mechanics: [\"filter\"]** — You explicitly need to filter across all three by category\n- **boundary: \"none\"** — Inherits from the contained modules; personal workspace with no external data sharing\n- **scale: 3** — A Block that composes three S2 groups into an interactive workspace. The grouping and filtering emerges at this scale; the individual tools (S2) don't have cross-filtering capability alone\n\nThe S2 modules stay intact and contained within this S3 dashboard. Their shared `contentType: \"tools\"` keeps them semantically grouped for filtering logic.","durationMs":14417}
